<br>
Simply put casters have many many ways of disingaging from combat without death and pure melees have none other than pulling the plug.<br>
<br>
Divine Aura<br>
Harm shield<br>
Shadowstep<br>
Yonder<br>
Gate<br>
Spirit of Cheetah<br>
<br>
and the big one...<br>
<br>
Running.  Due to melee range issues if poison has worn off or has been resisted its very hard to finish anyone who wants to run.<br>
<br>
Fact is a classes pvp success isn't just determined by the numbers of wins and losses but the extent of those wins and losses.  If you win 19 out of 20 fights but got not one kill and during the one loss you died and had your breastplate looted you not only lost but lost big time.<br>
<br>
It is essential that a class have some means of disengaging from some fights without dying.  With no means to disengage a class becomes useless in solo pvp not least because of the 2-4 member gang bang squads that are so prevelent.<br>
<br>
Now that I think of it this position may only be valid on rallos zek and only because of item loot.  On teams servers the difference between forcing someone to leave the zone in defeat and killing them would be a lot smaller, the fact that rogues have a difficult time finishing off non poisoned oponents (or at least I do) would be less meaningful,  and death to a group of 4 wizards would be less meaningful but for those of us on rallos zek who wont go around fully bagged anticipating defeat ,it is.<br>
<br>
It also occurs to me that perhaps i haven't explained this as well as I could have and perhaps you who read this see this as a defense of cowardice but until you have had to play in an environment where you have to fight again and again when a single defeat means the loss of something expensive and or hard to replace and at the same time watch countless casters shadowstep run or gate away even at very low hp I don't think you'll get it.<br>
<br>
Do NOT nerf melee gate )). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/2/01 4:59:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> <br>
I find it ridiculous when melee players complain about PvP. At least on Vallon Zek, they dominate the high level gameplay. I was doing well pet kiting a level 60 paladin yesterday with my 56 necro pet that had MR buff (so it resisted or broke most roots), well, except that the pet took heavy damage from the coldain ring dmg shield, and that pally eventually turned to pet and smacked it with a few hits from his epic. Note - pally fled eventually, which isn't very common.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
No, the big problem in PvP is the huge advantage that hybrids and melee's have towards casters and priests. Given how PvP works on the coin only servers, it is a joke that spell damage and pet damage is reduced to 66%, while melee damage, damage shields and archery, does 100% damage. <br>
<br>
All sorts of damage should have the same reduction. That would be a huge improvement for PvP balance.<br>
<br>
<br>
I do agree with some points on the list though, like bards poofing pets, and line of sight abusing.<br>
<br>
